outliers.value:
Exclusion criteria are as follows: 
- infants must attend to at least 50% of each familiarization event, from the beginning of the action to its completion; 
- subjects must also attend to at least 50% of each test event before the action is completed; - additional exclusion criteria: crying/fussiness, caregiver interference (distracting, readjusting, or talking to the infants), experimenter error (over or under-exposure to test stimuli), technical failure.

